.page-header
  %h1
    Welcome
    %small easily assemble your Vagrantconfig!


.row
  .span3
    = image_tag 'bento.jpg'
  .span9
    %blockquote
      %p Bento (弁当 bentō) [ˈbɛntəʊ] |
      A thin box, made of plastic or lacquered wood, divided into compartments which contain small separate dishes comprising a Japanese meal, esp lunch |

    %p.lead You can pack different ingredients, spices and a vagrant base box together to form a bentobox - <b>a complete Vagrantconfig file</b> ready to deploy!


    %dl.dl-horizontal
      %dt Bentobox
      %dd Represents a Vagrantconfig file consisting of a base box, ingredients and spices
      %dt Ingredient
      %dd Ingredients are configurations, an ingredient can consist of several chef cookbooks, shared folders, portmappings and can have a network configuration intended for the virtual machine
      %dt Spice
      %dd Spices are additional global configuration options for the Vagrantconfig file, with this you can, f.e. adjust the amount of RAM of the virtual machine
      %dt Base Box
      %dd Base boxes are virtual machine images packed and uploaded for later use

.row
  .span12
    %h2
      Download a bentobox!
      %small ready to use, just a <i>vagrant up</i> away!
    %ul.thumbnails
      - Bentobox.recent(5).all.each do |bentobox|
        %li.span2
          = link_to bentobox_url(bentobox,  params.merge(:format => :text, :download => true)), :class => "thumbnail", title: "Download Vagrantconfig" do
            = image_tag 'vagrant_pack.png'
            .caption
              %h3= bentobox.name
              %p= bentobox.description
